body: It's a NULL pointer exception. Is your program multiple threaded or single threaded?
Could you please help us reproduce the error? We need more information to debug it.
@snnn, I have update the issue report informaiton.

Please do not put Ort::Env or Ort Session into a static variable. 
Please free/destroy any ort variables when the main function ends.

If you're using pure C, then you have to call functions like ReleaseSession manually.
As you are using C++, the destructor of the objects will do the job for you.

Did removing 'static' solve the issue?
Sorry, it's a bug, we'll fix it.

issue.title: Disable delayload for cuda dlls

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: This change fixes #3129. 
**Motivation and Context**
- When running onnxruntime as dll on Windows, CUDA does some internal cleanups when process exits. After this, any call to CUDA would cause crash. Delayload makes thread_local destructor to happen after CUDA cleanup, thus the crash.
